    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "D&C",
        "delineation": "Section",
        "number": 31,
        "summary": "1\u20136, Thomas\u00a0B. Marsh is called to preach the gospel and is assured of his family's well-being; 7\u201313, He is counseled to be patient, pray always, and follow the Comforter.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Thomas, my son, blessed are you because of your faith in my work.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 52:22; 56:5 (5\u20136); 75:31.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, you have had many afflictions because of your family; nevertheless, I will bless you and your family, yea, your little ones; and the day cometh that they will believe and know the truth and be one with you in my church.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family; Unity.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Lift up your heart and rejoice, for the hour of your mission is come; and your tongue shall be loosed, and you shall declare glad tidings of great joy unto this generation.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 52:7 (7\u201310); Luke 2:10 (10\u201311); Rom. 10:15; Mosiah 3:3 (3\u20135).",
                        "start": 125,
                        "end": 129
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "You shall declare the things which have been revealed to my servant, Joseph Smith, Jun. You shall begin to preach from this time forth, yea, to reap in the field which is white already to be burned.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 18:19 (18\u201320); D&C 5:10; 42:12; 52:36.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 4:4 (4\u20136).",
                        "start": 171,
                        "end": 176
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore, thrust in your sickle with all your soul, and your sins are forgiven you, and you shall be laden with sheaves upon your back, for the laborer is worthy of his hire. Wherefore, your family shall live.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 14:15.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forgive.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 126:6; D&C 79:3.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 120
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 10:7 (3\u201311); D&C 51:14; 75:24; 84:79. TG\u00a0Consecration; Wages.",
                        "start": 145,
                        "end": 152
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, verily I say unto you, go from them only for a little time, and declare my word, and I will prepare a place for them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Children, Responsibilities toward.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, I will open the hearts of the people, and they will receive you. And I will establish a church by your hand;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Conversion.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And you shall strengthen them and prepare them against the time when they shall be gathered.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zech. 10:12; D&C 81:5; 108:7.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Be patient in afflictions, revile not against those that revile. Govern your house in meekness, and be steadfast.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 12:12. TG\u00a0Patience.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Affliction.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forbear; Malice; Retribution; Reviling.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Love within.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Steadfastness.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 112
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, I say unto you that you shall be a physician unto the church, but not unto the world, for they will not receive you.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Go your way whithersoever I will, and it shall be given you by the Comforter what you shall do and whither you shall go.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Comforter.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Pray always, lest you enter into temptation and lose your reward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prayer.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 14:38. TG\u00a0Temptation.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reward.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Be faithful unto the end, and lo, I am with you. These words are not of man nor of men, but of me, even Jesus Christ, your Redeemer, by the will of the Father. Amen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Steadfastness.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 2:10.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 28:20.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Authority of.",
                        "start": 140,
                        "end": 144
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}